An overview of issues and possible solutions regarding behavioural problems is given. Antisocial behavior - types, risk and protective factors and development trends. Criminal behaviour. Evidence-based prevention and intervention in the work with behavioural problems of children and youth in the educational context.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to create prerequisites for understanding and analysing the key topics regarding children and youth with behavioural problems in the educational context focusing on evidence-based prevention and intervention.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course, the student: - identifies, describes and assesses the types of behavioural problems of children and youth, risk and protective factors, development trends and ways of intervention; - has the prerequisites to apply evidence-based interventions while working with children and youth with behavioral problems.
